y-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tax1767361382425.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tax1767361382425.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tax1767361382425.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tax1767361382425\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the following guidelines to select the appropriate Layout Mode for your DSP based on\n\t\tyour development scenario:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tax1767361382425__ul_yc4_sx3_vhc\">\n<li class=\"li\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Generated Mode:</strong><p class=\"p\">Use when building new applications with component widgets,\n\t\t\t\t\trequiring automatic HTML structure handling, and minimal custom layout\n\t\t\t\t\trequirements.</p></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Fragment Mode:</strong>\n<p class=\"p\">Use when migrating existing DSPs to layout templates, combining legacy content\n\t\t\t\t\twith modern template systems, or implementing contained DSPs with custom layout\n\t\t\t\t\telements.</p></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Full Document Mode:</strong>\n<p class=\"p\">Use when maintaining existing applications without modification, requiring\n\t\t\t\t\tcomplete control over HTML document structure, or when no layout template\n\t\t\t\t\tintegration is needed.</p></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_27054641\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_27054641\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Choosing the Right Layout Mode Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 02, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Use the following guidelines to select the appropriate Layout Mode for your DSP based on your development scenario: Generated Mode: Use when building new applications with component widgets, requiring automatic HTML structure handling, and minimal custom layout requirements. Fragment Mode: Use when migrating existing DSPs to layout templates, combining legacy content with modern template systems, or implementing contained DSPs with custom layout elements. Full Document Mode: Use when maintaining existing applications without modification, requiring complete control over HTML document structure, or when no layout template integration is needed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}